  "prompt": "How do you invert your selection in Photoshop?",
  "response": "In Adobe Photoshop, you can invert your selection by following these steps:\n\n1. **Make an initial selection** using any of the selection tools (like the Marquee Tool, Lasso Tool, etc.).\n2. Go to the menu bar and click on **Select**.\n3. From the dropdown menu, choose **Inverse**. Alternatively, you can use the keyboard shortcut by pressing **Shift + Ctrl + I** (Windows) or **Shift + Command + I** (Mac).\n\nThis will invert your selection, meaning everything that was not selected will now be selected and vice versa.",
